                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/63.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1170fn1">Transmitted by the Department December 16 to the
                        Red Cross and the Mayor of El Paso.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 15, 1913</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>This morning the Spanish Minister at this capital called to ask me to have the
                    various authorities at El Paso, Texas, thanked for their kindness to Spanish
                    refugees at that place.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson O’Shaughnessy</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
